race.comment: PURE SILVER (11) looks well placed here coming back in grade. Outclassed in the Lee Steere Stakes at Ascot then midfield in richer company last time at Pinjarra. Will find this far easier and going much better than form suggests. Gets chance. Biggest danger looks to be UNIVERSAL HOTNESS (4). Led and was run down here two back then same again last time when stuck on well for third. Low draw and will take catching. LA EXCELLENCE (1) tackled a mile at Ascot last time and pushed forward from wide out before fading. Not a great day again but back in grade and can do much better. ANTZ PANTZ BABY (6) wasn't far away after a year long break and will strip far fitter. Blinkers go on and expecting sharp improvement. JAZALOT (7) was a close-up fourth latest. Mixing form but could sneak into the finish on best.
